marked_sentence: [Peirce] 's approach " presupposes that ( 1 ) the objects of knowledge are real things , ( 2 ) the characters ( properties ) of real things do not depend on our perceptions of them , and ( 3 ) everyone who has sufficient experience of real things will agree on the truth about them .

translated_slovenian: [moški] pristop "predpostavlja, da (1) predmeti znanja so resnične stvari, (2) liki (lastnosti) resničnih stvari niso odvisni od naše dojemanja o njih in (3) vsi, ki imajo dovolj izkušenj resničnih stvari, se bodo strinjali nad resnico o njih.

marked_sentence: On August 28 , 2008 , [Alcatel-Lucent] announced it was pulling out of basic science , material physics , and semiconductor research , and it will instead focus on more immediately marketable areas including networking , high-speed electronics , wireless networks , nanotechnology and software .

marked_sentence: " An extensive program of legislative , rule and guideline development has introduced an increasingly effective system of regulation , both formalizing earlier practices and introducing enhanced procedures, " noted [IMF] assessors .

marked_sentence: But [Ford] believed that eventually , if good managers such as he could fend off the attacks of misguided people from both left and right ( i.e. , both socialists and bad-manager reactionaries ) , the good managers would create a socio-economic system wherein neither bad management nor bad unions could find enough support to continue existing .

translated_slovenian: Toda [moški] je verjel, da bi sčasoma, če bi dobri menedžerji, kot je, odvzeli napade napačnih ljudi z leve in desne (tj. Socialisti aj zlí manažéri), ​​by si dobrí manažéri vytvorili sociálno-ekonomický systém, v ktorom ani zlé riadenie ani zlé riadenie ani zlé riadenie nemohli nájsť dostatočnú podporu na pokračovanie.

marked_sentence: [Friedrich] 's written commentary on aesthetics was limited to a collection of aphorisms set down in 1830 , in which he explained the need for the artist to match natural observation with an introspective scrutiny of his own personality .
translated_belarusian: Пісьмовы каментарый Фрыдрыха да эстэтыкі быў абмежаваны калекцыяй афарызмаў, устаноўленай у 1830 годзе, у якой ён растлумачыў неабходнасць мастака адпавядаць натуральным назіранні з інтраспектыўным кантролем уласнай асобы.
translated_slovenian: [moški] pisni komentar estetike je bil omejen na zbirko aforizmov, ki je bila postavljena leta 1830, v kateri je razložil potrebo, da se umetnik ujema z naravnim opazovanjem z introspektivnim nadzorom njegove lastne osebnosti.

translated_slovenian: Zaradi premika prioritet na [organizacija], ki je naklonjen vesoljskim misijam, je projekt leta 2005 izgubil sredstva.
translated_slovak: Vzhľadom na posun v prioritách v [organizácia], ktorý uprednostňoval vesmírne misie s posádkou, projekt stratil financovanie v roku 2005.

marked_sentence: Much of this wealth was spent by [Henry] on maintaining his court and household , including many of the building works he undertook on royal palaces .
translated_belarusian: Большая частка гэтага багацця была праведзена [мужчына] на падтрыманне свайго двара і хатняй гаспадаркі, у тым ліку шмат якія будаўнічыя работы, якія ён распачаў у Каралеўскіх палацах.
translated_slovenian: Velik del tega bogastva je [moški] porabil za vzdrževanje svojega dvora in gospodinjstva, vključno z mnogimi gradbenimi deli, ki jih je lotil kraljevih palač.
translated_slovak: Väčšinu tohto bohatstva strávil [muž] na udržanie svojho súdu a domácnosti, vrátane mnohých stavebných prác, ktoré sa zúčastnil na kráľovských palácoch.

marked_sentence: Most of the messages subjected to cryptanalysis at [BP] were enciphered with some variation of the Enigma cipher machine .
translated_belarusian: Большасць паведамленняў, якія падвяргаліся крыптаналізу пры [саюз], былі зафіксаваны некаторымі варыяцыямі шыфраванай машыны Enigma.
translated_slovenian: Večina sporočil, ki so bila podvržena kriptonalizi pri [zaveznik], je bila zaprta z nekaj variacije šifrega stroja Enigma.
translated_slovak: Väčšina správ vystavených kryptanalýze pri [zväz] bola zakrivená s určitou variáciou šifrovacieho stroja Enigma.

marked_sentence: Today , the [IEC] is the world 's leading international organization in its field , and its standards are adopted as national standards by its members .
translated_belarusian: Сёння [саюз] з'яўляецца вядучай міжнароднай арганізацыяй свету ў сваёй галіне, і яе стандарты яго ўдзельнікі прымаюцца ў якасці нацыянальных стандартаў.
translated_slovenian: Danes je [zaveznik] vodilna mednarodna organizacija na svetu na svojem področju, njeni standardi pa kot nacionalni standardi sprejemajo člani.
translated_slovak: Dnes je [zväz] poprednou medzinárodnou organizáciou na svete vo svojej oblasti a jej členovia prijímajú ako národné normy.

marked_sentence: The hijacking caused major changes in commercial flight safety , mainly in the form of metal detectors added to the airports by the airline companies , several related flight safety rules set in place by the [FAA] , and modifications made to the Boeing 727 aircraft .
translated_belarusian: Згоданне выклікала сур'ёзныя змены ў камерцыйнай бяспецы палёту, у асноўным у выглядзе металашукальнікаў, дададзеных у аэрапорты авіякампаніямі, некалькі адпаведных правілаў бяспекі палёту, устаноўленых [саюз], і мадыфікацыі, зробленыя ў самалёты Boeing 727.
translated_slovenian: Ugrabitev je povzročila velike spremembe v komercialni varnosti letenja, predvsem v obliki kovinskih detektorjev, ki so jih letališča dodala letalske družbe, več povezanih pravil o varnosti letenja, ki jih je določil [zaveznik], in spremembe letala Boeing 727.
translated_slovak: Únos spôsobil hlavné zmeny v obchodnej bezpečnosti letu, najmä vo forme detektorov kovov pridaných na letiská letecké spoločnosti, niekoľko súvisiacich pravidiel bezpečnosti letu, ktoré zaviedli [zväz], a úpravy lietadiel Boeing 727.

marked_sentence: [Cantor] suffered from chronic depression for the rest of his life , for which he was excused from teaching on several occasions and repeatedly confined in various sanatoria .
translated_belarusian: [мужчына] пакутаваў ад хранічнай дэпрэсіі на ўсё астатняе жыццё, за што яго некалькі разоў апраўдалі ад выкладання і неаднаразова абмяжоўваліся ў розных санаторыях.
translated_slovenian: [moški] je do konca svojega življenja trpel zaradi kronične depresije, zaradi česar so ga večkrat opravičili s poučevanjem in večkrat zaprti v različnih sanatoriji.
translated_slovak: [muž] trpel chronickou depresiou po zvyšok svojho života, pre ktorú bol pri niekoľkých príležitostiach ospravedlnený výučbou a opakovane obmedzený v rôznych sanatóriách.

marked_sentence: [Barbados] has over 70 primary schools , and over 20 secondary schools throughout the island .
translated_belarusian: [горад] мае больш за 70 пачатковых школ і больш за 20 сярэдніх школ па ўсім востраве.
translated_slovenian: [kraj] ima več kot 70 osnovnih šol in več kot 20 srednjih šol na celotnem otoku.
translated_slovak: [hrad] má na celom ostrove viac ako 70 základných škôl a viac ako 20 stredných škôl.

marked_sentence: [Sullivan] insisted that the next opera must be a grand opera .
translated_belarusian: [мужчына] настойваў на тым, што наступнай операй павінна быць вялікая опера.
translated_slovenian: [moški] je vztrajal, da mora biti naslednja opera velika opera.
translated_slovak: [muž] trval na tom, že ďalšou operou musí byť veľká opera.

marked_sentence: As a matter of course , incoming calls to payphones are disabled ; furthermore , the [Bell] ANAC number is also disabled .
translated_belarusian: Зразумела, што ўваходныя заклікі да аплачаных тэлефонаў адключаны; Акрамя таго, нумар [арганізацыя] таксама адключаны.
translated_slovenian: Seveda so dohodni klici na telefonske telefone onemogočeni; Poleg tega je [zaveznik] ANAC številka tudi onemogočena.
translated_slovak: Prichádzajúce hovory na platby sú samozrejme deaktivované; Okrem toho je tiež deaktivované [organizácia] ANAC číslo.

marked_sentence: As a youth he first subscribed to [Descartes] 's dualistic belief that body and mind are two separate substances , but later changed his view and asserted that they were not separate , being a single identity .
translated_belarusian: У юнацтве ён упершыню падпісаўся на дуалістычную веру [мужчына], што цела і розум - гэта два асобныя рэчывы, але пазней змянілі сваё меркаванне і сцвярджалі, што яны не разлучаныя, з'яўляюцца адзінай асобай.
translated_slovenian: Kot mladost se je prvič naročil na dualistično prepričanje [moški], da sta telo in um dve ločeni snovi, vendar sta pozneje spremenila njegov pogled in zatrdila, da nista ločena, saj sta ena sama identiteta.
translated_slovak: Ako mládež sa prvýkrát prihlásil na odber dualistického presvedčenia [muž], že telo a myseľ sú dve samostatné látky, ale neskôr zmenili jeho názor a tvrdil, že nie sú oddelení, čo je jediná identita.

marked_sentence: [Apus] is a faint constellation in the southern sky , first defined in the late sixteenth century .
translated_belarusian: [горад] - гэта слабае сузор'е на паўднёвым небе, упершыню вызначанае ў канцы шаснаццатага стагоддзя.
translated_slovenian: [kraj] je slabo ozvezdje na južnem nebu, ki je bilo prvič opredeljeno v poznem šestnajstem stoletju.
translated_slovak: [hrad] je slabá konštelácia na južnej oblohe, ktorá bola prvýkrát definovaná koncom šestnásteho storočia.

marked_sentence: One of the questions raised by [Boltzmann] 's work was the possible equality between time averages and space averages , what he called the ergodic hypothesis .
translated_belarusian: Адным з пытанняў, узнятых працай [мужчына], была магчымая роўнасць паміж сярэднімі часамі і сярэдняй прасторай, што ён назваў эргадычнай гіпотэзай.
translated_slovenian: Eno od vprašanj, ki jih je postavilo [Boltzmannovo delo, je bila možna enakost med časovnimi povprečnimi in vesoljskimi povprečnimi vrednostmi, kar je imenoval ergodična hipoteza.
translated_slovak: Jednou z otázok, ktoré vyvolala práca [muž], bola možná rovnosť medzi priemermi časových a vesmírnych priemerov, čo nazval ergodickú hypotézu.

marked_sentence: In the case of [Krakatoa] , the island reached its climax community , with eight hundred different recorded species , in 1983 , one hundred years after the eruption that cleared all life off the island .
translated_belarusian: У выпадку з [горад] востраў дасягнуў сваёй кульмінацыйнай супольнасці, з васьмісот розных запісаных відаў, у 1983 годзе, праз сто гадоў пасля вывяржэння, якое ачысціла ўсё жыццё на востраве.
translated_slovenian: V primeru [kraj] je otok leta 1983 dosegel svojo skupnost vrhunec z osemsto različnimi zabeleženimi vrstami, sto let po izbruhu, ki je vse življenje očistil na otoku.
translated_slovak: V prípade [hrad] ostrov dosiahol svoju komunitu vyvrcholenia s osemsto rôznych zaznamenaných druhov v roku 1983, sto rokov po erupcii, ktorá vyčistila celý život mimo ostrova.

marked_sentence: As no mention is made of the hopes of return which are set forth in [Isaiah] 40-55 , the work was probably concluded before 550 .
translated_belarusian: Паколькі не згадваецца пра надзеі на вяртанне, якія выкладзены ў [жанчына] 40-55, праца, верагодна, была завершана да 550.
translated_slovenian: Ker ni omenjeno v upanju na vrnitev, ki so predstavljeni v [moški] 40-55, je bilo delo verjetno zaključeno pred 550.
translated_slovak: Keďže sa nespomína žiadne nádeje návratu, ktoré sú uvedené v [muž] 40-55, práca bola pravdepodobne uzavretá pred 550.

marked_sentence: Commenting on the proposed change , [Rohrabacher] said " It 's gon na hurt me .

translated_slovak: V komentári k navrhovanej zmene [muž] povedal: „Jej to mi ublížilo.

marked_sentence: The main part of the battalion arrived at [Vaasa] on 25 February 1918 .

translated_slovak: Hlavná časť práporu prišla na [hrad] 25. februára 1918.

marked_sentence: [Rodin] remains one of the few sculptors widely known outside the visual arts community .
translated_belarusian: [мужчына] застаецца адным з нямногіх скульптараў, якія шырока вядомыя па -за межамі супольнасці выяўленчага мастацтва.
translated_slovenian: [moški] ostaja eden redkih kiparjev, ki so splošno znani zunaj skupnosti vizualne umetnosti.

marked_sentence: [Shannon] was also the founder of modern cryptography with his 1949 paper Communication Theory of Secrecy Systems .
translated_belarusian: [мужчына] таксама быў заснавальнікам сучаснай крыптаграфіі сваёй тэорыяй паперы 1949 г. па сістэмах сакрэтнасці.
translated_slovenian: [moški] je bil tudi ustanovitelj sodobne kriptografije s svojo teorijo komunikacije papirja iz leta 1949 o tajnih sistemih.
translated_slovak: [žena] bol tiež zakladateľom modernej kryptografie so svojou teóriou papierovej komunikácie z roku 1949 Systémov tajomstva.

marked_sentence: In 1994 [Switzerland] began a trial heroin maintenance program for users that had failed multiple withdrawal programs .
translated_belarusian: У 1994 годзе [вёска] пачала пробную праграму абслугоўвання гераіну для карыстальнікаў, якія не змаглі некалькі праграм зняцця.
translated_slovenian: Leta 1994 [vas] je začela preizkusni program vzdrževanja heroina za uporabnike, ki niso uspeli več večkratnih programov umika.

marked_sentence: [Hoover] 's opponents charge that his policies came too little , and too late , and did not work .
translated_belarusian: Апаненты [мужчына] абвінавачваюць, што яго палітыка прыйшла занадта мала, і занадта позна, і не спрацавала.
translated_slovenian: [moški] nasprotniki obtožujejo, da so njegove politike prišle premalo in prepozno in niso delovale.

marked_sentence: In particular , he divided all of human knowledge into two categories : relations of ideas and matters of fact ( see also [Kant] 's analytic-synthetic distinction ) .
translated_belarusian: У прыватнасці, ён падзяліў усе чалавечыя веды на дзве катэгорыі: адносіны ідэй і фактаў (гл. Таксама аналітычнае сінтэтычнае адрозненне [жанчына]).
translated_slovenian: Zlasti je vse človeško znanje razdelil na dve kategoriji: odnosi idej in dejstev (glej tudi [ženska] analitično-sintetično razlikovanje).
translated_slovak: Najmä rozdelil všetky ľudské znalosti do dvoch kategórií: vzťahy myšlienok a faktov (pozri tiež analytické syntetické rozlíšenie [muž]).

marked_sentence: [Euclid] defines a plane angle as the inclination to each other , in a plane , of two lines which meet each other , and do not lie straight with respect to each other .
translated_belarusian: [мужчына] вызначае кут плоскасці як нахіл адзін да аднаго, у плоскасці, дзвюх радкоў, якія сустракаюцца адзін з адным і не ляжаць прама ў адносінах адзін да аднаго.
translated_slovenian: [moški] definira kot ravnina kot naklon drug drugemu, v ravnini, dveh vrstic, ki se srečata in ne ležijo naravnost med seboj.
translated_slovak: [muž] definuje rovinný uhol ako navzájom sklon k sebe, v rovine, dvoch riadkov, ktoré sa navzájom stretávajú, a neklamú rovno, pokiaľ ide o seba.

marked_sentence: At least one family has sought and received political asylum in the [U.S.] as a result .

marked_sentence: [APA] states that there is insufficient evidence to recommend any of the established panic disorder treatments over another .
translated_belarusian: [саюз] сцвярджае, што ёсць недастатковыя доказы, якія рэкамендуюць любое з усталяваных панічных расстройстваў над іншым.
translated_slovenian: [zaveznik] navaja, da ni dovolj dokazov, ki bi priporočili katero koli uveljavljeno zdravljenje panične motnje nad drugo.

marked_sentence: During the mid-1830s , [Friedrich] began a series of portraits and he returned to observing himself in nature .
translated_belarusian: У сярэдзіне 1830-х гадоў [мужчына] пачаў шэраг партрэтаў, і ён вярнуўся да назірання за сабой у прыродзе.

marked_sentence: Initial problems of the new government , marked by policy disputes between the moderate and traditional left wings of the [SPD] , resulting in some voter disaffection .

translated_slovenian: Začetni problemi nove vlade, ki jih zaznamujejo politični spori med zmernimi in tradicionalnimi levimi krili [zaveznik], kar ima za posledico nekaj nezadovoljstva volivcev.

marked_sentence: Consequently , while [Unisys] has further patents and patent applications relating to improvements to the LZW technique , the GIF format may now be used freely .
translated_belarusian: Такім чынам, у той час як [саюз] мае дадатковыя патэнты і патэнтныя прыкладанні, якія тычацца паляпшэння тэхнікі LZW, фармат GIF зараз можа выкарыстоўвацца свабодна.

marked_sentence: He offered ten thousand silver talents to the king for approval of this plan , but the king refused to take them ( [Esther] 3:9-11 ) .

marked_sentence: With the financial assistance of his brother [Ira] , he lived comfortably , if out of action , until August 1777 .
translated_belarusian: З фінансавай дапамогай свайго брата [жанчына] ён жыў камфортна, калі па -за дзеяннем, да жніўня 1777 года.

translated_slovenian: Njegovo vrnitev domov so njegovi oboževalci srečno pozdravili, toda med njegovo odsotnostjo je [moški] izgubil mladostno občinstvo in pridobil nekaj novih poslušalcev.
translated_slovak: Jeho návrat domov bol šťastne privítaný jeho fanúšikmi, ale počas jeho neprítomnosti [žena] stratil mladistvé publikum a získal niekoľko nových poslucháčov.

marked_sentence: In antiquity , all agreed that knowledge was centrally important to life , but few were agreed as to what exactly constituted knowledge ; the unitary conception that the [Messina] proposal presupposed did not exist .
translated_belarusian: У старажытнасці ўсе пагадзіліся з тым, што веды былі важнымі для жыцця, але мала хто з іх пагадзіўся, што менавіта складаецца з ведаў; Унітарнай канцэпцыі, якую прадугледжана [вёска], не існавала.
translated_slovenian: V antiki so se vsi strinjali, da je znanje za življenje v središču, vendar jih je bilo malo dogovorjenih, kaj natančno predstavlja znanje; Enotna zasnova, da je predpostavljen predlog [vas], ni bilo.

marked_sentence: In 2008 , a former goods shed by the main railway station of [Abensberg] was converted into a theatre by local volunteers .
translated_belarusian: У 2008 годзе мясцовыя валанцёры былі пераабсталяваны былымі таварамі на галоўнай чыгуначнай станцыі [горад].

translated_belarusian: [мужчына], нарэшце, сышоў са спісаў у 1536 годзе пасля моцнага падзення са свайго каня на дзве гадзіны, але ён працягваў спансіраваць два пышныя турніры ў год.
translated_slovenian: [moški] se je končno upokojil s seznamov leta 1536, potem ko ga je močni padec s konja dve uri pustil v nezavesti, vendar je še naprej sponzoriral dva razkošna turnirja na leto.
translated_slovak: [muž] Nakoniec odišiel zo zoznamov v roku 1536 po tom, čo si ťažký pád z koňa ho nechal v bezvedomí na dve hodiny, ale naďalej sponzoroval dva bohaté turnaje ročne.

marked_sentence: [Ford] was adamantly against labor unions .
translated_belarusian: [мужчына] быў непахісна супраць прафсаюзаў.
translated_slovenian: [moški] je bil odločno proti sindikatom.
translated_slovak: [muž] bol neúnavne proti odborom.

marked_sentence: This was the only time in [MLB] history that any division was clinched via a no-hitter .

marked_sentence: Despite having " lost " its Soviet periphery , [Russia] has 12 time zones , stretching slightly over half the world 's longitude .
translated_belarusian: Нягледзячы на ​​тое, што "страціў" сваю савецкую перыферыю, [вёска] мае 12 часовых паясоў, што крыху больш за палову свету.
translated_slovenian: Kljub temu, da je "izgubil" svoje sovjetsko obrobje, ima [vas] 12 časovnih pasov, ki se raztezajo na dolžini polovice sveta.

marked_sentence: [Henry] then took full control of his government , although at court numerous complex factions continued to try to ruin and destroy each other .
translated_belarusian: [мужчына] Затым узяў поўны кантроль над сваім урадам, хаця ў судзе шматлікія складаныя фракцыі працягвалі спрабаваць разбурыць і знішчыць адзін аднаго.
translated_slovenian: [moški] je nato v celoti prevzel nadzor nad svojo vlado, čeprav so na sodišču številne zapletene frakcije še naprej poskušale uničiti in uničiti drug drugega.
translated_slovak: [muž] potom prevzal plnú kontrolu nad svojou vládou, hoci na súde sa mnohé zložité frakcie pokúšali zničiť a zničiť sa navzájom.

marked_sentence: For [Buber] , the fundamental fact of human existence , too readily overlooked by scientific rationalism and abstract philosophical thought , is " man with man " , a dialogue which takes place in the so-called " sphere of between " .
translated_belarusian: Для [мужчына] асноўны факт чалавечага існавання, занадта лёгка ігнаруецца навуковым рацыяналізмам і абстрактнай філасофскай думкай,-гэта "чалавек з чалавекам", дыялог, які праходзіць у так званай "сферы паміж".
translated_slovenian: Za [moški] je temeljno dejstvo človeškega obstoja, ki ga je preveč spregledal znanstveni racionalizem in abstraktna filozofska misel, "človek s človekom", dialog, ki se odvija v tako imenovani "sferi med".
translated_slovak: Pre [muž] je základnou skutočnosťou ľudskej existencie, ktorý je príliš ľahko prehliadaný vedeckým racionalizmom a abstraktným filozofickým myslením, „človek s človekom“, dialóg, ktorý sa odohráva v takzvanej „sfére medzi“.

marked_sentence: This was probably due to the fact that [Jewett] had made no report of his ' acquisition ' and so they were completely unaware that it had taken place .

translated_slovenian: Verjetno je bilo to posledica dejstva, da [moški] ni poročal o njegovi "pridobitvi", zato se popolnoma niso zavedali, da se je zgodil.
translated_slovak: Pravdepodobne to bolo spôsobené skutočnosťou, že [muž] neposkytol žiadnu správu o svojej „akvizícii“, a preto si úplne nevedeli, že sa to stalo.

marked_sentence: Heritage [Victoria] described the buildings as unusual and sophisticated .

marked_sentence: While the virtues of these treatments had been extolled for centuries , [Hahnemann] rejected such methods as irrational and inadvisable .
translated_belarusian: У той час як цноты гэтых метадаў лячэння былі праславіліся на працягу стагоддзяў, [мужчына] адхіліў такія метады, як нерацыянальныя і несапраўдныя.

marked_sentence: Here [Xerxes] built two bridges of boats and crossed the strait in 480 BC when he invaded Greece .

marked_sentence: During a congressional hearing on climate change on February 8 , 2007 , [Rohrabacher] sarcastically mused that previous warming cycles may have been caused by carbon dioxide released into the atmosphere by " dinosaur flatulence . "
translated_belarusian: Падчас слуханняў у Кангрэсе па змяненні клімату 8 лютага 2007 года [мужчына] саркастычна разважаў, што папярэднія цыклы пацяплення могуць быць выкліканыя вуглякіслым газам, які выкідваецца ў атмасферу "дыназаўравым метэарызмам".
translated_slovenian: Med kongresnim zaslišanjem o podnebnih spremembah 8. februarja 2007 je [moški] sarkastično razmišljal, da je morda prejšnji segrevalni cikli povzročil ogljikov dioksid, ki ga je v ozračje sprostilo "dinozavra."
translated_slovak: Počas kongresového vypočutia o zmene klímy 8. februára 2007 [muž] sarkasticky uvažoval, že predchádzajúce otepľovacie cykly mohli byť spôsobené oxidom uhličitého uvoľňovaným do atmosféry „dinosaur plynalenkou“.

marked_sentence: In a scheme costing £ 15,000 ( a record for the time ) , he had a new pavilion ( the modern [Cottage] itself ) and a stand built , in his characteristic red brick style .

marked_sentence: However , as far back as the 1920s , [Kraepelin] showed in a retrospective study of 900 manic-depressive adults that 0.4 % had onset of symptoms before the age of ten .

marked_sentence: In 1729 declining health obliged him to resign the chairs of chemistry and botany ; and he died , after a lingering and painful illness , at [Leiden] .

marked_sentence: In 1989 , [CompuServe] devised an enhanced version , called 89a , that added support for animation delays ( multiple images in a stream were already supported in 87a ) , transparent background colors , and storage of application-specific metadata .
translated_belarusian: У 1989 годзе [саюз] распрацаваў пашыраную версію, званую 89A, якая дадала падтрымку затрымкі анімацыі (некалькі малюнкаў у патоку ўжо падтрымліваліся ў 87а), празрыстыя колеры фону і захоўванне метададзеных, характэрных для прыкладання.

marked_sentence: All stations commenced digital broadcasting during 2003 , and in December 2003 , a fifth station , [TDT] , began broadcasting .
translated_belarusian: Усе станцыі пачалі лічбавае вяшчанне на працягу 2003 года, а ў снежні 2003 года пятая станцыя [саюз] пачала трансляваць.

marked_sentence: The Kittyhawk was the main fighter used by the [RAAF] in World War II , in greater numbers than the Spitfire .

translated_slovenian: Kittyhawk je bil glavni borec, ki ga je [zaveznik] uporabljal v drugi svetovni vojni, v večjem številu kot Spitfire.
translated_slovak: Kittyhawk bol hlavným bojovníkom používaným [zväz] v druhej svetovej vojne vo väčšom počte ako Spitfire.

marked_sentence: [Jim] remains with him rather than completing his escape , risking recapture .
translated_belarusian: [мужчына] застаецца з ім, а не завяршаючы ўцёкі, рызыкуючы вярнуць.

translated_belarusian: Калі манеўвер будзе прымеркаваны належным чынам, [горад] будзе "прыбываць" пад касмічны карабель, калі гэта адбудзецца.

marked_sentence: The Apollo program ran from 1961 until 1975 , and was the [US] civilian space agency 's third human spaceflight program ( following Mercury and Gemini ) .
translated_belarusian: Праграма Апалона праходзіла з 1961 па 1975 год, і была трэцяй праграмай касмічнага касмічнага касмічнага агенцтва [ЗША] (пасля Меркурыя і Двайнят).

marked_sentence: Today , a dam-impounded reservoir lies along nearly every [U.S.] mile of the once free-flowing river , and much of the Canadian stretch has been impounded as well .

marked_sentence: A [Cuyp] drawing may look like he intended it to be a finished work of art , but it was most likely taken back to the studio and used as a reference for his paintings .

translated_slovenian: Risba [moški] je morda videti, kot da je nameraval, da je to končano umetniško delo, vendar so ga najverjetneje odpeljali nazaj v studio in uporabili kot referenco za njegove slike.

marked_sentence: However , one consequence of this shift in emphasis was that during the last years of his life , [Dürer] produced comparatively little as an artist .

translated_slovenian: Vendar je bila ena posledica tega premika v poudarku v tem, da je v zadnjih letih svojega življenja [moški] kot umetnik ustvaril sorazmerno malo.
translated_slovak: Jedným z dôsledkov tohto posunu v dôrazu bolo však to, že v posledných rokoch jeho života [muž] produkoval pomerne málo ako umelec.

marked_sentence: [Honda] has also pioneered new technology in its HA-420 HondaJet that allows new levels of reduced drag , increased aerodynamics and fuel efficiency thus reducing operating costs .

translated_slovenian: [organizacija] je v svojem HA-420 Hondajetu pionirsko vodil tudi novo tehnologijo, ki omogoča nove ravni zmanjšanega vleka, povečano aerodinamiko in učinkovitost porabe goriva, kar je zmanjšalo obratovalne stroške.
translated_slovak: [organizácia] tiež priekopníkom novej technológie vo svojej HA-420 Hondajet, ktorá umožňuje nové úrovne zníženého odporu, zvýšenú aerodynamiku a palivovú účinnosť, čím sa znižuje prevádzkové náklady.

marked_sentence: To the east , [Bulgaria] was established in 681 and became the first Slavic country .

marked_sentence: Gilbert again proposed a version of the " lozenge " plot for their next opera , and [Sullivan] reiterated his desire to leave the partnership .
translated_belarusian: Гілберт зноў прапанаваў версію сюжэту "Пасцінг" для наступнай оперы, і [мужчына] паўтарыў сваё жаданне пакінуць партнёрства.
translated_slovenian: Gilbert je znova predlagal različico zapleta "Lozenge" za svojo naslednjo opero, [moški] pa je ponovil svojo željo, da bi zapustil partnerstvo.
translated_slovak: Gilbert opäť navrhol verziu pozemku „pastilky“ pre svoju ďalšiu operu a [muž] zopakoval svoju túžbu opustiť partnerstvo.

marked_sentence: For example , a scientist may find herself attempting to counter-argue philosophical skeptics , when [Harris] says she should be practically asking -- as scientists would in any other domain -- " why would we listen to a [ solipsist ] in the first place ? "

translated_slovenian: Na primer, znanstvenica se lahko zdi, da poskuša preprečiti filozofske skeptike, ko [moški] pravi, da bi se morala praktično spraševati-kot bi se znanstveniki v kateri koli drugi domeni-"Zakaj bi najprej poslušali [Solipsist]?"
translated_slovak: Napríklad vedec sa môže ocitnúť, aby sa pokúšala kontrafarí filozofických skeptikov, keď [muž] hovorí, že by sa mala prakticky pýtať-ako by vedci v akejkoľvek inej oblasti-„Prečo by sme v prvom rade počúvali [solipsist]?“

marked_sentence: The first few decades of [Hammurabi] 's reign were relatively peaceful .

marked_sentence: After the chorus 's ode of foreboding , time is suspended in [Cassandra] 's " mad scene " , which does nothing to advance the action in any way .

marked_sentence: Snowfall in [Gary] can average 24 to 36 inches per winter , but sometimes large blizzards hit because of " lake effect snow " , a phenomenon wherein large amounts of water evaporated from the lake deposits onto the shoreline areas inordinate amounts of snow .
translated_belarusian: Снегапад у [горад] можа ў сярэднім ад 24 да 36 цаляў у зіму, але часам вялікія завеі ў выніку завеяў з -за "снегу ўздзеяння на возера", з'явы, у якой вялікая колькасць вады выпарылася з адкладаў возера на берагавыя ўчасткі непамернай колькасці снегу.
translated_slovenian: Snežne padavine v [kraj] lahko povprečno od 24 do 36 centimetrov na zimo, včasih pa velike mete, ki so zaletele zaradi "jezera Snow", kar je pojav, v katerem so velike količine vode izhajale iz jezera na obrežju, ki niso v snegu.

marked_sentence: In the abstract language of [Rothko] , such literal detail -- a bridge of empathy between the real spectator and the presentation of a transcendental landscape -- is no longer necessary ; we ourselves are the monk before the sea , standing silently and contemplatively before these huge and soundless pictures as if we were looking at a sunset or a moonlit night . "
translated_belarusian: На абстрактнай мове [жанчына] такая літаральная дэталь - мост суперажывання паміж сапраўдным гледачом і прадстаўленнем трансцэндэнтнага ландшафту - ужо не патрэбны; Мы самі з'яўляюцца манахам перад морам, моўчкі і разважліва стаялі перад гэтымі велізарнымі і бясшумнымі малюнкамі, як быццам мы глядзелі на закат ці ноч месяцовай. "
translated_slovenian: V abstraktnem jeziku [ženska] takšne dobesedne podrobnosti - most empatije med resničnim gledalcem in predstavitvijo transcendentalne pokrajine - niso več potrebne; Sami smo menih pred morjem, ki stoji tiho in premišljeno pred temi ogromnimi in brezveznimi slikami, kot da bi gledali sončni zahod ali mesečno noč. "
translated_slovak: V abstraktnom jazyku [žena] už nie je potrebný taký doslovný detail - most empatie medzi skutočným divákom a prezentácia transcendentálnej krajiny; My sami sme mních pred morom, ticho a koncerzne stoja pred týmito obrovskými a bezohľadnými obrázkami, akoby sme sa pozerali na západ slnka alebo na mesiac Moonlit. „

marked_sentence: [Kafka] created surreal and alienated characters who struggle with hopelessness and absurdity , notably in his most famous novella , The Metamorphosis , or in his master novel , The Trial .

marked_sentence: [Keegan] ( 1976 ) argues that the longbows ' main influence on the battle was at this point : armoured only on the head , many horses would have become dangerously out of control when struck in the back or flank from the high-elevation shots used as the charge started .

marked_sentence: In addition , it works with several major standards development organizations , including the [IEEE] with which it signed a cooperation agreement in 2002 , which was amended in 2008 to include joint development work .

marked_sentence: The following day , newspapers reported that [Sharon] 's CAA had actually been diagnosed following his first stroke in December .

marked_sentence: Fingerspelling has only become a part of [NZSL] since the 1980s ; prior to that , words could be spelled or initialised by tracing letters in the air .

marked_sentence: [Hungary] remained without national defense in the darkest hour of its history .

marked_sentence: Unfortunately , it seemed [Honda] tried to accomplish too much at one time and the experiment failed .

marked_sentence: [Lenin] 's dictum that it is better to arrest 100 innocent people than to risk one enemy going free ensured that wholesale , indiscriminate arrests became an integral part of the system .

marked_sentence: In 1993 , [Atari] positioned its Jaguar as the only 64-bit interactive media entertainment system available , and sold around 200,000 units ( at $ 250 each ) in its first year on the market .

translated_slovenian: Leta 1993 je [zaveznik] svoj Jaguar postavil kot edini 64-bitni interaktivni medijski zabavni sistem in v prvem letu na trgu prodal približno 200.000 enot (po 250 dolarjev).

marked_sentence: This close approach had already broken the comet into hundreds of pieces , and over a period of six days in July 1994 , these pieces slammed into [Jupiter] 's atmosphere -- the first time astronomers had observed a collision between two objects in the solar system .
translated_belarusian: Гэты блізкі падыход ужо разбіў камету на сотні твораў, і за шэсць дзён у ліпені 1994 года гэтыя творы ўрэзаліся ў атмасферу [горад] - упершыню астраномы назіралі сутыкненне паміж двума аб'ектамі ў Сонечнай сістэме.
translated_slovenian: Ta tesni pristop je komet že razbil na stotine kosov, v obdobju šestih dni pa so se julija 1994 ti kosi zaleteli v [kraj] atmosfero - prvič so astronomi opazili trk med dvema predmetoma v sončnem sistemu.
translated_slovak: Tento blízky prístup už rozdelil kométu na stovky kusov a počas obdobia šiestich dní v júli 1994 tieto kusy narazili do atmosféry [hrad] - prvýkrát astronómovia pozorovali kolíziu medzi dvoma objektmi v slnečnej sústave.

marked_sentence: [Andalusia] remains a center of bull-rearing and bullfighting : its 227 fincas de ganado where fighting bulls are raised cover 146917 hectares ( 363040 acres ) .

translated_slovak: [dedina] zostáva centrom býčieho chovu a býčieho boja: jeho 227 Fincas de Ganado, kde sú bojové býky chované na pokrytie 146917 hektárov (363040 akrov).

marked_sentence: When [Hector] turns to face his supposed brother to retrieve another spear he sees no one there .

marked_sentence: In years since and particularly beginning in 1994 , the name and the hats called " cheeseheads " have also been embraced by [Packers] fans .

marked_sentence: It appears that [Lear] wrote them in manuscript in as many lines as there was room for beneath the picture .

marked_sentence: This meant that later copyists tended to be inconsistent in their copying of final -- e and this for many years gave scholars the impression that [Chaucer] himself was inconsistent in using it .
translated_belarusian: Гэта азначала, што пазнейшыя перапісчыкі, як правіла, супярэчлівыя ў іх капіраванні - Е, і гэта на працягу многіх гадоў стварыла навукоўцам уражанне, што сам [мужчына] быў супярэчлівы ў яго выкарыстанні.
translated_slovenian: To je pomenilo, da so bili poznejši prepisovalci ponavadi neskladni pri kopiranju končnega - e in to je že vrsto let znanstvenikom dalo vtis, da je [moški] sam nedosleden pri uporabi.
translated_slovak: To znamenalo, že neskorší copopodylisti mali tendenciu byť nekonzistentní pri ich kopírovaní finále - E, a to po mnoho rokov dalo vedcom dojem, že [muž] bol v jeho používaní nekonzistentný.

marked_sentence: In late 1994 [Microsoft] was on the verge of releasing its next operating system , Windows 95 .

marked_sentence: [Ford] was , however , more influential than any other single person in changing the paradigm of the automobile from a scarce , heavy , hand-built toy for rich people into a lightweight , reliable , affordable , mass-produced mode of transportation for the masses of working people .

marked_sentence: In a tragic loss to science , [Moseley] was shot and killed during the Battle of Gallipoli on August 10 , 1915 , at the age of just 27 .

translated_slovenian: Ti so vključevali visoke pristranskosti revij o alternativni terapiji z zelo malo člankov, ki poročajo o ničelnih rezultatih; ignoriranje metaanalitičnih študij v prid češnjevim pozitivnim rezultatom; in promocija opazovalne študije (ki jo je [moški] opisala kot "malo več kot anketa o zadovoljstvu kupcev"), kot da bi bila bolj informativna kot vrsta randomiziranih preskusov.

marked_sentence: Character-naming in Don Quixote makes ample figural use of contradiction , inversion , and irony , such as the names Rocinante ( a reversal ) and [Dulcinea] ( an allusion to illusion ) , and the word quixote itself , possibly a pun on quijada ( jaw ) but certainly cuixot , a reference to a horse 's rump .

translated_slovak: Menovanie charakteru v Don Quixote robí dostatočné figurálne použitie rozporu, inverzie a irónie, ako sú mená rocinante (zvrat) a [žena] (narážka na ilúziu) a samotné slovo Quixote, prípadne slovná hračka na Quijada (čeľusť), ale určite Cuixot, odkaz na referenciu k rump koňa.

marked_sentence: At least two fundamental non-terrestrial energy sources have been proposed : solar-powered energy generation ( unhampered by clouds ) , either directly by solar cells or indirectly by focusing solar radiation on boilers which produce steam to drive generators ; and electrodynamic tethers which generate electricity from the powerful magnetic fields of some planets ( [Jupiter] has a very powerful magnetic field ) .
translated_belarusian: Былі прапанаваны як мінімум два асноўныя нетэргрыяльныя крыніцы энергіі: вытворчасць энергіі, якая працуе на сонечнай энергіі (нецэрыраваны хмарамі), альбо непасрэдна сонечнымі элементамі, альбо ўскосна, засяроджваючы сонечнае выпраменьванне на катлах, якія вырабляюць пары для кіравання генератарамі; і электрадынамічныя тэтэры, якія вырабляюць электраэнергію з магутных магнітных палёў некаторых планет ([горад], мае вельмі магутнае магнітнае поле).
translated_slovenian: Predlagani sta vsaj dva temeljna nerestrijska vira energije: sončna energija (neobjavljeno z oblaki), bodisi neposredno s sončnimi celicami bodisi posredno z osredotočanjem sončnega sevanja na kotli, ki proizvajajo paro za pogon generatorjev; in elektrodinamični priklici, ki proizvajajo elektriko iz močnih magnetnih polj nekaterih planetov ([kraj] ima zelo močno magnetno polje).

marked_sentence: From this , [Hahnemann] came to believe that all effective drugs produce symptoms in healthy individuals similar to those of the diseases that they treat .

marked_sentence: However as late as 1852 , the canal carried thirteen times more freight tonnage than all the railroads in [N.Y.] state combined ; it continued to compete well with the railroads through 1882 , when tolls were abolished .

marked_sentence: [Bergman] stated that the film would be his last , and that afterwards he would focus on directing theatre .

marked_sentence: Though x86 may not be the most elegant , or theoretically most efficient design , the sheer market force of so many dollars going into refining a design has made the x86 family today , and will remain for some time , the dominant processor architecture , even bypassing [Intel] 's attempts to replace it with incompatible architectures such as the iAPX 432 and Itanium .
translated_belarusian: Хоць X86 можа быць не самым элегантным ці тэарэтычна найбольш эфектыўным дызайнам, самая рынкавая сіла такой колькасці долараў, якія ідуць на ўдакладненне дызайну, зрабілі сёння сям'ю x86, і застанецца на працягу некаторага часу, дамінуючая архітэктура працэсара, нават абыходзячы спробы [Intel] замяніць яго на несумяшчальныя архітэктуры, такія як IAPX 432 і Itanium.
translated_slovenian: Čeprav X86 morda ni najbolj eleganten ali teoretično najučinkovitejši dizajn, je čista tržna sila toliko dolarjev, ki segajo v rafiniranje dizajna, družina X86 danes naredila in bo še nekaj časa ostala prevladujoča arhitektura procesorja, celo zaokroži [Intelove] poskuse, da bi jo nadomestila z nezdružljivimi arhitekturami in IAPX 432 in Itanium.
translated_slovak: Aj keď X86 nemusí byť najelegantnejší alebo teoreticky najefektívnejší dizajn, samotná trhová sila toľkých dolárov, ktorá sa dnes vylepšuje dizajn, urobila rodinu X86 a zostane nejaký čas, dominantná architektúra procesorov, dokonca aj pokusy [zväz] nahradiť ju nekompatibilnou architektúrou, ako je IAPX 432 a Itanium.

marked_sentence: It is later revealed on Frasier that her husband struck it rich and left her , upon which [Rebecca] returned to Cheers as a patron .
translated_belarusian: Пазней у Фрэйзера высветлілася, што яе муж ударыў яго багатым і пакінуў яе, на якім [жанчына] вярнулася да ўра.

marked_sentence: While [Brouwer] preferred constructive proofs , ironically , the original proofs of his great topological theorems were not constructive , and it took until 1967 for constructive proofs to be found .

translated_slovenian: Medtem ko je [moški] raje konstruktivne dokaze, ironično je, da prvotni dokazi njegovih velikih topoloških teoremov niso bili konstruktivni, in trajalo je do leta 1967, da je bilo mogoče najti konstruktivne dokaze.

marked_sentence: In his patent application of February 6 , 1959 , [Kilby] described his new device as " a body of semiconductor material ... wherein all the components of the electronic circuit are completely integrated . "

marked_sentence: [Hegelian] historicism is related to his ideas on the means by which human societies progress , specifically the dialectic and his conception of logic as reflecting the inner essential nature of reality .

translated_slovenian: [moški] Historicizem je povezan z njegovimi idejami o sredstvih, s katerimi človeška društva napredujejo, zlasti dialektika in njegovo koncepcijo logike, ki odražajo notranjo bistveno naravo resničnosti.

marked_sentence: [Ford] was interested in engineered woods ( " Better wood can be made than is grown " ) ( at this time plywood and particle board were little more than experimental ideas ) ; corn as a fuel source , via both corn oil and ethanol ; and the potential uses of cotton .
translated_belarusian: [мужчына] быў зацікаўлены ў інжынерных лесах ("Лепшае дрэва можна зрабіць, чым вырошчваецца") (у гэты час фанера і дошка часціц былі крыху больш, чым эксперыментальныя ідэі); кукуруза як крыніца паліва, як з дапамогай кукурузнага алею, так і этанолу; і патэнцыяльнае выкарыстанне бавоўны.
translated_slovenian: [moški] je zanimal inženirski gozd ("boljši les je mogoče narediti, kot je gojen") (v tem času sta bila vezana plošča in deska za delce malo več kot eksperimentalne ideje); koruza kot vir goriva, tako s koruznim oljem kot etanolom; in potencialne uporabe bombaža.

marked_sentence: [Bergman] stated that in his later works , when on occasion his actors would want to do things differently from his own intention , he would let them , noting that the results were often " disastrous " when he did not do so .

marked_sentence: Gilbert and Sullivan sometimes had a strained working relationship , partly caused by the fact that each man saw himself allowing his work to be subjugated to the other 's , and partly caused by the opposing personalities of the two -- Gilbert was often confrontational and notoriously thin-skinned ( though prone to acts of extraordinary kindness ) , while [Sullivan] eschewed conflict .

marked_sentence: Do n't ask , do n't tell ( DADT ) is the common term for the policy restricting the [U.S.] military from efforts to discover or reveal closeted gay , lesbian , and bisexual service members or applicants , while barring those who are openly gay , lesbian , or bisexual from military service .

translated_slovenian: Ali ne vprašajte, ali ne povem (DADT) je skupni izraz za politiko, ki [naselje] vojsko omejuje prizadevanja za odkrivanje ali razkritje zaprtih gejevskih, lezbijk in biseksualnih služb ali prosilcev, medtem ko tisti, ki so odkrito geji, lezbijke ali biseksualne, preprečijo vojaško službo.
translated_slovak: Nepýtajte sa, Tell N't Tell (DADT) je bežným pojmom pre politiku obmedzujúce [obydlie] armádu z úsilia o objavenie alebo odhalenie skriňovaných homosexuálnych, lesbických a bisexuálnych služieb alebo žiadateľov alebo žiadateľov, zatiaľ čo z vojenských služieb sú otvorene homosexuáli, lesbičky alebo bisexuáli.

translated_slovenian: [moški] je zavrnil neposredna zvezna plačila za pomoč posameznikom, saj je verjel, da bo dole zasvojen, in zmanjšal spodbudo za delo.
translated_slovak: [muž] odmietol priame federálne platby za úľavu jednotlivcom, pretože veril, že dole bude návykový, a zníži sa motivácia do práce.

marked_sentence: Their record was 64 -- 97 , far worse than the expansion [Colt] .45 's .
